definitions.definition: A Turkic -speaking people in South Central Siberia, who lives along the upper reach of the Yenisei River north of the Sayan Mountains.

main_definition: A Turkic -speaking people in South Central Siberia, who lives along the upper reach of the Yenisei River north of the Sayan Mountains.

main_definition: A Yenisei Turkic language spoken by the Khakas people.
